INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '1) To make the dough: Combine all of the dough ingredients and mix and knead them, by hand, mixer, or bread machine, until you have a soft, smooth dough.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '2) Allow the dough to rise, covered, for about 2 hours, or until it''s puffy and nearly doubled in bulk.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '3) Gently deflate the dough, and transfer it to a lightly greased work surface.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '4) Pat and roll the dough into a rectangle about 18" x 14".');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '5) Make the cinnamon filling: Mix the cinnamon sugar with some melted butter and water to make a paste OR mix the Baker''s Cinnamon Filling and water to make a smooth paste.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '6) Looking at the dough horizontally (so it''s 18" long), spread half the filling down the center third of the dough');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '7) Slice each banana into about 12 rounds. Space the slices atop the filling.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '8) Fold one of the end pieces into the center to cover the bananas and filling.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '9) Spread the remaining filling atop the piece of dough you''ve just folded into the center, and distribute the dried pineapple evenly atop the filling.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '10) Fold the other side of the dough over the filling to cover it. Pull the long side seam underneath, and tuck each end underneath, too. You should have a long, flat log with no filling showing.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '11) Use a sharp knife to cut 4 diagonal slashes atop the loaf, cutting through both layers of dough; this will allow steam to escape.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '12) Brush with the beaten egg white, and sprinkle with the coarse or Demerara sugar.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '13) Cover the loaf gently with lightly greased plastic wrap, and allow it to rest for 1 hour. It won''t rise much, if at all. Towards the end of the resting period, preheat the oven to 375°F.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '14) Bake the loaf in the middle of the oven for 25 minutes. Tent with foil, and bake for an additional 20 to 25 minutes, till it''s golden brown and a sharp knife poked into the center doesn''t reveal any raw dough.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '15) Remove from the oven, and transfer to a rack to cool.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1242, 'Yield: 1 large loaf, about 16 servings.');
