INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '2) In a medium bowl, mix together the coconut, coconut cream, salt, and coconut flavor, stirring till thoroughly combined.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '3) Add the coconut milk powder, stirring to combine.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '4) Drop the sticky mixture in ping pong-sized balls (about 1 1/2") onto the prepared baking sheets. It helps to use a tablespoon cookie scoop or small ice cream scoop here. For best results, pack the coconut mixture into the scoop; each ball should weigh about 1 ounce. You can space the balls fairly close together on the baking sheet; they only need about 3/4" to 1" between them.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '5) Bake the macaroons for about 10 minutes; they won''t brown. You may see the merest hint of brown on top.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '6) Remove from the oven, and cool completely on the baking sheet.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '7) To make the coating, heat the chocolate chips, butter, and corn syrup until the chips are very soft. A microwave oven works well, as does a saucepan set over very low heat.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '8) Dip half of each cooled macaroon into the chocolate. Set the macaroons back on the baking sheet, and allow the chocolate to set completely before serving. To store, place in one layer in a closed container. They''ll keep for 2 or 3 days, but will gradually become less moist as they sit.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, 'Yield: 33 macaroons.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, '');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, 'tips from our bakers');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, 'Coconut cream, sweetened condensed coconut milk, is the coconut equivalent of sweetened condensed milk. Substitute sweetened condensed milk, if desired.');
INSERT INTO preparationSteps (recipe_id, step) VALUES (1243, 'Coconut milk powder adds flavor and helps the macaroons hold their nice, smooth shape. Leave it out if you like.');
